SIMPLE: touchwood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Touchwood
<hw>Touch"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably for
<ets>tachwood</ets>; OE. <ets>tache</ets> tinder (of uncertain origin) +
<ets>wood</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Wood so decayed as to serve for tinder; spunk, or
punk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Dried fungi used as tinder; especially, the
<spn>Polyporus igniarius</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Touchy</ent>⟦br⟧
